sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe Router
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant Pod as vllm-rocm Pod
    participant GPU as AMD ROCm GPU
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>(PVC / S3)
    participant HF as Hugging Face Hub<br/>(optional)

    Note over Pod,S3: Flow 3: Model Loading at Startup
    Pod->>S3: Load model weights<br/>Filesystem (PVC) or HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+ / IAM credentials
    S3-->>Pod: Model artifacts
    Pod->>HF: Download tokenizer (optional)<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
    HF-->>Pod: Tokenizer files
    Pod->>GPU: Load model into GPU memory<br/>PCIe/ROCm
    GPU-->>Pod: Model ready

    Note over Client,Pod: Flow 1: OpenAI-compatible HTTP Inference
    Client->>Pod: POST /v1/completions<br/>HTTP/8000 TCP<br/>No encryption (pod-level)
    Pod->>GPU: Inference computation<br/>PCIe/ROCm
    GPU-->>Pod: Generated tokens
    Pod-->>Client: JSON response<br/>HTTP/8000 TCP

    Note over Client,Pod: Flow 2: TGIS gRPC Inference
    Client->>Pod: gRPC GenerationService<br/>gRPC/8033 TCP<br/>No encryption (pod-level)
    Pod->>GPU: Inference computation<br/>PCIe/ROCm
    GPU-->>Pod: Generated tokens
    Pod-->>Client: gRPC response<br/>gRPC/8033 TCP
